# Frontend Agent -- MeetingBox Dashboard

## Domain
You own the React SPA under `frontend/src/`. The dashboard is served as static files by the FastAPI backend at port 8000.

## Architecture
- **React 18** + **TypeScript** + **Vite** build
- **Zustand** for state management (3 stores: auth, meeting, action)
- **Tailwind CSS** + **Headless UI** for styling
- **Axios** for HTTP calls to `/api/*` endpoints
- **WebSocket** at `/ws` for real-time events from Redis
- **React Router v6** for client-side routing

## Key Files
- `App.tsx` -- Root component, routing, onboarding guard
- `pages/` -- Dashboard, MeetingDetail, LiveRecording, Settings, SystemStatus, Onboarding
- `api/client.ts` -- Axios instance with interceptors
- `api/meetings.ts`, `api/actions.ts`, `api/settings.ts`, `api/integrations.ts` -- API modules
- `store/authStore.ts`, `store/meetingStore.ts`, `store/actionStore.ts` -- Zustand stores
- `hooks/useWebSocket.ts` -- Auto-reconnecting WebSocket hook
- `components/ui/` -- Reusable UI primitives (Button, Card, Modal, Badge, etc.)
- `types/` -- TypeScript type definitions

## API Base URL
All API calls go to the same origin (relative URLs). WebSocket connects to `ws://${window.location.host}/ws`.

## Coding Standards
- Never leave `console.log` / `console.warn` / `console.error` in production code
- Every page must have loading, error, and empty states
- Use proper TypeScript types -- avoid `any` and unchecked type assertions
- Clean up all side effects (intervals, timeouts, WebSocket) in useEffect return
- Use Tailwind utility classes, no inline styles
- All lists should use stable unique keys (not array index)
- Handle null/undefined defensively -- use optional chaining and nullish coalescing
- Error boundaries should wrap route-level components
